{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7513464e-d516-444b-948b-003a1f01a9c3","content":"Good news — with .NET 10 SDK, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform **natively**. The `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property is no longer needed and can be removed.\n\nYour `EnableMSTestRunner` is still required (it builds the test project as an executable using MTP). Here's the cleanup:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01AZboMK5E7A77zcBTFLxtyA","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Removing obsolete MTP property"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_012kxRKpZyrAiw4t4RN9k3p1","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-ef6f29a17fbb409a897c4a76d6a1acb0/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"    <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n","new_str":"\n"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-ef6f29a17fbb409a897c4a76d6a1acb0/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"a8364064-b707-436b-b23c-8027d74f1818","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is on .NET 10 SDK (10.0.100) and is using MSTest with `EnableMSTestRunner` and `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` set to true.\n\nIn .NET 10, `dotnet test` natively supports Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MTP) without needing the `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` property. The .NET 10 SDK has built-in MTP integration, so `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` is no longer needed and can be removed.\n\nLet me provide the guidance and make the change.","outputTokens":429,"requestId":"082E:16A6CA:7F83F38:8DC1DFF:69EABF79"},"id":"0ba3ece8-f3cc-457f-91dd-3e9670c3110a","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:55:29.083Z","parentId":"58bd1d71-d226-4844-8085-a75b0ef01bde"}
